						<summary>

						<p>A slab set up in Survey No. 1/2, about 1(1/2) miles to the east of the village.</p>						

						<p>SĀDHĀRAṆA.</p>						

						<p>(18th century.)</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription can be assigned to 18th century on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>States that the pillar <hi rend="italic">(kaṁbhaṁ)</hi> demarcates the boundry between the three villages Kirttipalle <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Timmarājapuram, Uruṭūru and Peddanapāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
